furicam (1.3.3-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Jpeg reencoding has been stripped and quality labels are more vague because HAL does not make percentages available to my knowsledge
  * HDR images are captured in burst mode making it much quicker
  * Additionally the EV 0 frame gets saved separately in case the HDR image ends up being worse
  * HDR images each get a UUID in case two HDR shots are fired really close together
  * Continous AF is restored 5 seconds after tapping to focus
  * Zoom can go below 1.0x but cannot be tested because no FuriLabs phone has an ultrawide as of now
  * Also a fix regarding CameraSession handling

 -- nico359 <124350776+nico359@users.noreply.github.com>  Tue, 30 Jun 2026 13:39:00 +0200

furicam (1.3.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * HDR memory optimizations: remove synthetic bracket fallback, downscale
    to 50% before MergeMertens, upscale with Lanczos4, aggressive mat release
    - peak memory cut from ~2GB to ~300MB
  * Widen HDR EV brackets from ±2 to ±3 stops for more aggressive dynamic range
  * Use EV 0 frame's ISO (from EXIF) for bracket exposures instead of hardcoded 400,
    preventing highlight clipping in bright scenes
  * Fix HDR EXIF copy: use EV 0 frame metadata instead of EV -3 (dark frame)
  * Fix resolution dropdown sync when switching cameras (per-camera memory)
  * Match HDR output filename to regular photo naming: IMG_..._HDR.jpg

 -- nico359 <124350776+nico359@users.noreply.github.com>  Sun, 28 Jun 2026 14:27:00 +0200

furicam (1.3.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix A/V sync: hold audio samples until first video frame is muxed
  * Fix gallery: videos appear immediately after recording (recordingSaved signal)
  * Fix gallery: ffmpeg video thumbnails (QImage registration, ffmpeg in deps)
  * Fix gallery: delete jumps to previous entry instead of empty slot
  * Fix macro camera: clamp JPEG output to sensor max resolution on camera switch
  * Fix macro camera: wait for async session close before re-opening (race fix)
  * Fix AE FPS range: allow HAL to trade framerate for exposure in low light
  * Add video bitrate floors per resolution (10/20/40 Mbps for ≤720p/≤1080p/4K)

